{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, how to generate functionally correct and safe code is challenging.• Benchmarks.",
    "Existing benchmarks for code generation mainly include hand-written programming problems and their corresponding solutions (such as HumanEval).",
    "However, there is a huge difference between these human-written benchmarks and real projects.",
    "In addition, the human-written benchmarks are time-consuming and strongly dependent on experts' knowledge.",
    "Thus, constructing a benchmark from real projects automatically is important for code generation.• Hallucination of LLMs."
  ]
}